< text>
Awesome place to go for back issues.  Tons of books to look through and it's fun to dig for those issues you've been looking for. I spent two days there and still wasn't able to look through everything. More than reasonable pricing and the co-owner Timmy is a super cool guy. </record>
</dataset><record>
<date>1546989645626< /date><rate>1</rate>< UserId.>
105744036212704438928< /UserId.>
<Text>I honestly don't understand what all these great reviews are talking about.  This shop is not what I look for in a comic shop. I don't usually rate businesses, but I'd hate for someone to read all these great reviews and be fooled like I was so here goes.

Went into this shop and it looked pretty nice. Totally gave the illusion that it was organized and well kept. But to me, it was just organized chaos(generously). The books were really grimy and weren't really in any order other than "Marvel" "DC" some had letters on them like "Marvel A-C" but were still out of order because there were many books in those boxes that had nothing to do with the labels.
So you have to really search for what you want. I noticed books aren't really priced. Well they are, but the prices are from old bags and apparently aren't honored. If you manage to sift through all of these books and find what you're looking for you'll see a price guide at check out. I understand that some shops opperate this way, but I personally feel that it is poor business. It makes me as the customer feel that I have done all of the hard work going through their chaos and finding more valuable books only to have them decide at the register what I will pay. Knowing that I'm not going to do all that work for nothing so I end up buying their books instead of just putting them back.

I've seen a few [what I believe to be] honest reviews, but the rest just don't seem to reflect my experience here. I will be staying away from this shop in the future

*As a business suggestion I think they should put up a sign that says "Prices on comics bag do not reflect store prices charged"</Text>< Gmap_id>
0x809467503f7710eb:0xc150a90d24360e6e< /Gmap_id>
<pics>None< /pics><user_name>Tim Reyes</user_name>< response>
{'time': 1546997045762, 'text': 'I do apologize if you had a bad experience. We took over the shop a year ago and have been working very hard to organize.\n\nThe boxes of comics on the wall might be labeled DC or MARVEL a-z, but they are organized by title and number.\n\nAnd although the wall books in the back are not bagged and boarded, or priced, we always let customers know they are only $2.00.\n\nThe previous owner did not believe on bags and boards, so I am sure that as a comic collector, you know how pricey it is to bag and board all of the books we have.\nOn average, we bag and board 2000 a month, and as you can see we have a long way to go still.\n\nAs for the price guide, yes we do have one at the front desk - every comic store/dealer owns one. This is the only way one can judge the correct pricing for their books. It is not just a benefit to us, but many customers who ask to see it.\n\nVery rarely do we pull the book out in front of customers,  unless they ask a value of a book they are collecting, or are selling books. As said above, books that are on the wall unpriced are all $2.00\n\nThere are times when a customer wishes to purchase a book that is priced,  and we dont honor the price marked - because we discount the item for them\n\nAgain, I am sorry you had a bad experience.'}</response>

<user_id>117165343145465256067< /user_id><rate>5< /rate>< Review>
Restoring an older Acura and not only did Extreme Auto Parts have the exact glove box I was looking for, they took the time to work with me and verify some detailed aspects of it with additional photos.  Also as the glove box is susceptible to damage in transit, I asked them to overpack and then shrink wrap the glove box as I am on the other side of the country from Extreme Auto and née it was going to be a rough journey through the Fedex ground carrier.  When the glove box arrived today, the packaging was nothing short of a piece of art as the guys in the shipping department literally shaped the box in or origami like folds around the overpacking of the glove box that was then shrink wrapped and the packed in this beautiful form of a box that was obviously packed by a professional in the shipping department who really takes their job seriously and artfully.   I know I’m gushing about the way it was packaged, however I rarely get salvaged parts in such exquisite condition or shipped with such care. I’m sure your like me and are really upset when you order a product only to find it was destroyed in transit because someone in the shipping department simply did not have the right resources to do their job right or simply just did not care.  This was not the case and the  glove box arrived in pristine condition just like the photos supplied by Extreme prior to my purchase.  This was my first purchase with these guys and the whole experience simply reminds me of how everyone used to care about their job and take pride in their service and product.   Well if this first purchasing experience was any indication, I have found a great company to work with in connection with my auto restoration part needs.   Old world service, pride and care in the modern world today pretty much sums up my first experience with Extreme.<//Review>

< Review>
We were on the hunt for a good restaurant for dinner recently and we ended up at Chula Vista Farmers Table. This is a new location for this restaurant in this city. We were seated promptly and was greeted by our friendly and attentive hostess. We ordered an assortment of dishes, from chicken to salads to pasta. The food was very tasty and memorable. This restaurant is on the pricey side but we do understand that quality costs money. We will be back for brunch one of these days<//Review>

<userid>112654326561437033883< /userid>< date>
1627100472377</date>
< review>
I feel a responsibility to the people of southern San Diego to provide reviews that critically critique food, service, experience, and atmosphere, so the citizens of America's finest city can spend their hard-earned money on a restaurant worthy of patronage.

It is with great pleasure and pride in my community that I award Farmers Table with 5 golden stars. When we arrived with a reservation my wife and I were seated immediately! We reviewed the menu and were advised by the servers on some great options for beer and popular cocktails. My wife was stuck between 2 beers to order. The servers brought us samples so she could make a more educated choice and selected an airy Belgian beer. I ordered a blueberry moonshine cocktail. Both of these drinks were stupendous and set the tone for a night of luxury and impeccable flavors.

The sampling of drinks was the only start of the amazing service. For our meal, we ordered some specials - a surf and turf for my wife and game of the day for myself. My steak was seared with divine intervention. It melted in my mouth and the fat was perfectly rendered. My wife's steak, to her dismay, was slightly overcooked. We informed the server and the chefs promptly seared a new stake to her liking. The gravy was an exquisite blend of chocolate and red wine glazed over the meat like a chocolate dream.

For my wife's stake being slightly overcooked, our Server provided a desert free of charge. A bread pudding topped with a scoop of vanilla ice cream and a few fresh strawberries and blueberries drizzled on the plate. The desert was incredible - I am not typically a fan of bread pudding and I ate most of it.

I feel so much guilt for not having the vocabulary to describe how incredible our experience at Farmer's Table was. Kudos to the staff, the chef, and the managers of this new location. You have earned two loyal customers and I am proud to say Chula Vista has a new affordable and high-quality restaurant in our neighborhood.

Thank you so much for the great evening.< /review>

< Review>
I want to start by saying I'm not suggesting you shouldn't visit this place because I'm all about supporting small business.. I just want to add that if have high expectations you might be disappointed. I Really wanted to like this place! The service was great and very cute decor. It has a lot of potential too but if you want to charge on the higher end then your food needs to carry more flavor and finesse. We came for brunch and Food was completely bland and packets of Ketchup and tapatio were thrown on top.  Bread was barely toasted and not even buttered or butter on the side. We had to ask. They claim to be using organic and high quality ingredients but then they give you a processed coffee cream packets. It just made it feel like you were at a Dennys paying the double the price. Their truffle arugula potatoes were the best out of the whole meal but you have to pay extra for that. I hope they consider adding fresh salsa instead of tapatio and organic creamer to go with the organic coffee.</Review>

< Text>
The food, service and overall ambiance is good.
The Chula Vista Farmer's Table must be having a soft opening, and I'm sorry to say not a great one. I've been there Saturday afternoon and Sunday morning. Both times have been good. Don't get me wrong, it's been good. But if you are one of the unfortunate people that have a bad experience is because of the management of the servers.
Again, don't get me wrong. My servers were great and we'll trained, so far none of them have been amateurs. But they did seem stretched thin. They really did their best and can not be blamed. I'm sure it's due to the opening of a new restaurant and not sure of the tempo of the neighborhood.

All that to say, give the location a few more weeks or months and they'll fit perfectly in our little neighborhood of Chula Vista.
The food is a little pricey but the food was good. I'm glad to have another place to go to for breakfast... Now I just have to try their dinner 😁</Text>

< text>
This is my third time here. I really love their man candy bacon and their breakfast sandwich. Today unfortunately the service was a little bit off.  I ordered a meal with an egg and I requested for it to be cooked over hard. When food was brought everything was great, except the egg was over medium. i really don't like my told to be even soft, let alone runny. I returned it requested it again and it was over medium/hard. They asked me if I wanted anything else. The waitress was very kind, but I was okay. Lost my appetite. The manager came out with a whole new dish with the egg cooked correctly. He apologized and explain how he himself cooked the egg just to make sure that it would be perfect. I felt bad but I was really appreciative of the effort the staff made to correct the problem. All I can say is they have really great service here and the food is really good. Definitely coming back :).< /text>

Very attentive service, and our breakfast dishes were rich.

(Original)
Very attentive service, and all four of us enjoyed our breakfast.

Over half the menu is American comfort food, but there are many other dishes with things like goat cheese or truffle oil, which they also prepare well.

Surprise: the chilaquiles were great - crisp and with very zesty green (tomatillo) sauce.

Good attention to ventilation as well.

</record></dataset><record>
<UserId.>109695979005672789686< /UserId.><username>Neal C</username>< Time>
1564887198443< /Time>
<rate>4< /rate>< text>
Really good service and tasty food. The ambiance is modern /clean as well.

We ordered the chili fried chicken and the spicy drypot. The chicken was the perfect level of spicy. I think it could've been a little crispier, but it was still really good.

The drypot had great flavor but the imitation Crabstick and tofu skin got quite shredded/broken in the cooking process, which made it a pain to eat. They could also improve the menu by stating that you get 6 items with the dry/hotpot as it doesn't say that any items come with the drypot and I heard several other tables asking this question.

Overall, will be back for the great food and service (although if we get drypot again we'll adjust what we order!).<//text>

It used to be one of my favorites in this area that I visit every week, but not anymore.

Since they changed the chef in May, everything has changed. Dishes are now salty, oily yet lack of flavor.

I gave three attempts since their chef change to see whether it's just a one-time bad luck, only to find out that the way they cook has been inconsistent but consistently low quality.

I've finally reached a conclusion that it's not the same restaurant anymore and I'm not going back.</review>

< username>
Queenanie Nguyen< /username>
<text>Came here on Labor day weekend and was not disappointed with our choice. Food came out fast, was tasty, and had a wide variety to satisfy everyone’s cravings.

FOOD: 5/5
We had spicy chicken, eggplant with string beans, Yang Zhou fried rice and Shezhuan lamb.

I liked that they didn’t douse everything in spice. For example, the lamb was mixed in with vegetables and green chili; by itself it wasn’t spicy, but if you can handle spice, kick it up with the chili peppers. Similarly with fried chicken. So everyone can eat up to their desired spice level.

Didn’t get their dry spice pot or the seafood mix (coz we didn’t think we could finish it). Will update this review once we try it.

SERVICE: 5/5
To be fair, we came in before the “official” opening hours. They said they would reopen at 5pm for dinner, but we got in at 4:45. Not high time for dinner in Sunset. So service was all good.

LOCATION/DECOR: 4/5
Clean, minimal decor. At a good location in town for Shezhuan food. Can be hard to find parking.

Overall highly recommended.</text>< rating>
5</rating>

<UserId.>116039240238449860468<//UserId.><Name>Vicky Gu</Name><Time>1557945490808< /Time><rate>4< /rate>< Text>
They used to be called a different name, lollipop. In my opinion, a much better name than the new name. It serves not only Szechuan food, but also food from other regions.  It is always a nice experience coming here, they offer peanuts as a starter while you are ordering, if you are hungry, that is much needed.  Restaurant is clean and bright, TV is fun to watch as we don’t have access to the Chinese cooking shows normally.  Food is solid, 4/5,  not the best Chinese food that you can have in town, but solid.  They are flavorful, decent portion size, offers enough options for spicy and non spicy.   The deserts are pretty nice too, we always end our meal with a few deserts. to me, desert is the highlight here.</Text>

<name>Jason Moreno<//name><date>1583266466794</date>< Resp>
None<//Resp>
< rating>
5< /rating>
< Review>
I've had a AAA membership since I was 18 and see no reason to not have one. If I only use it to register my car it's worth it, but I've gotten my passport photos and have gotten travel info here as well.

The parking lot can be a bit of a pain to get into with where the building is located. You must enter going north bound on Mendocino. The lot is actually very small but I still never have a hard time finding a spot.
They take your name and reason for being there rather quickly as you enter. They have a Keurig for coffee and tea.

After putting my name on the list, getting my coffee and taking a seat,  I have never waited longer than 10 minutes, if that.

The only thing I would change is the location and size of the parking lot, but a smaller lot and a hard to get into driveway means shorter wait times I guess. So take the good with the bad.

*New*
Follow @WhatsEatingMo
Twitter  - IG - YouTube
Subscribe to our new Podcast< /Review>

< Text>
I've been an AAA member for 15 years. When I arrived to the Mendocino Ave branch office, I checked in and was able to sit with a hot cup of coffee from their Keurig coffee maker while I waited for my name to be called.
I needed a title transfer for a new truck we purchased.  The representative that assisted me with my title transfer was very fast. With all the slow downs of the computer, It took all of 10 minutes, tops.
I asked her about insurance for the vehicle and she put me in the queue to speak with an insurance agent.
With him, I was able to add my new car, talk about my minor daughter being on our insurance, and about programs to reduce rates for her/us.
The entire staff made the visit worthwhile and I'll be visiting again.<//Text>

<text>My coach was absolutely fantastic and the program will work if you implement it.  I was recently asked by a colleague if I recommend the program and I told him, yes BUT...just know and accept you are in a strict contract.

I was on fire my first 4-5 months doing everything my coach told me and building my pipeline. By the end of  the fifth month I let my coach know my health was not doing well and I couldn’t get myself to implement the program because it felt like my Brian was shutting off.  For the second part of the year I couldn’t implement anything I was learning because I could not work.  Unfortunately according to customer service I could not suspend my account until I felt better so I kept pushing to break though like I was advised to do.  Eventually I began to lose my vision and found out I didn’t have an organization/work motivation problem, I have Multiple Sclerosis and brain damage.

I would never blame Tom Ferry Organization for this, as my health is not their issue.  My warning is, you are in contract and you may end up paying for 6 months of a program you physically can’t do.  By the end I literally lost my vision enough that I wasn’t allowed to drive.  At this point I quit early because I could not see. I have no hard feelings, but knowing I could relapse once recovered I would never join again.

That being said, if you are healthy and motivated you will be successful.  Just be sure you are physically and mentally up for it!  The contract suspends for no one (at least that was my understanding from the customer service rep).</text>< response>

<GmapID>0x80dcdee814b67acb:0xab3c840a65627f02< /GmapID><review>I got my real estate license 3 years ago out of necessity. I was a single mom trying to survive on a teacher's salary and my children's needs/wants were quickly outgrowing my income. I have always had a passion for real estate, an entrepreneurial spirit, and the desire to help people, so I decided real estate would be a great income supplement. My first year in real estate was mediocre, but the few commission checks I received definitely made things much easier financially as a single mom. In my second year, 2016, I was able to close 25 deals (about 6 million in volume) while still teaching full-time. A little over a year ago, at the end of 2016, as I entered my third year in real estate, I joined coaching and my coach helped me to develop a business plan that gave me the confidence I needed to leave teaching and go "all-in" on real estate. This past year, with the help and guidance of my coach, I changed brokerages twice (super stressful when you're a producing agent) and started a team near the end of the year. I now have a full-time Operations Director, two full-time Buyer Specialists, and a part-time Buyer Specialists who will join us full-time this summer. I credit Tom, my coaches and the support of this amazing ecosystem for my success. I ended up closing 40 transactions (just under 10 million in volume), in spite of the stress involved with changing brokerages, building a team, and continuing to produce. My team and I will close over 100 transactions in 2018, our first full year as a team, then my goal is to join Team+ coaching. The perception of real estate Agents at times becomes a bit distorted as our customers are under the impression that this endeavor provides a lucrative income for little to no work.   Nothing could be farther from the truth.   Only the best Agents are successful, and this success is measured by their knowledge of the market, an understanding of economics, land values, property taxes, local politics, and the numerous laws which must be followed.   More importantly, as Agents, we need to understand human psychology to deal with people’s emotions and motivations.  We must stand out above the crowd, and to meet these daily challenges, I highly recommend Tom Ferry’s Coaching.   It is an investment in self, an investment in your personal success, as it provides tools for thinking “outside of the box”.   Through the coaching platform you must answer to a higher discipline, to be true to self, and maintain a consistent effort for success.    Even with 15 years real estate experience, my Coach has opened doors, given me greater self-confidence, and allowed me to meet those challenges that can only occur when there is an interaction with people.   If you want to be a successful agent don’t look to the financial gain, but for the personal reward of helping individuals finding that perfect home.  We are a people business.   The training by Tom Ferry and his experienced Coaches can make that happen, they give you that knowledge and confidence to build a great business.< /text>

<Review>I felt the need to share my initial experience about the Tom Ferry coaching program.   I have been an agent for just over two full years and have had good success but felt that I could do more.  I have thought about coaching for sometime but I always justified to my self reasons not to do it.  When I decided 2018 was going to be my coaching year, I spoke to 5 different coaching companies and drilled them on policies, content, success rate, personalities etc.  I spoke to a guy name Timmy Han several times here at Tom Ferry coaching.  I found him to be the most upfront, honest, and amazing caring person of all of them. He did not sugar coat things.  He pushed me yet was understanding, helpful and mindful of my concerns and feelings.  He promised me that he personally would follow up with me during coaching and that he would do everything he could to get me a coach that not only is a great coach with a long line of personal success but also one that has a track record of taking her coaching clients from zero to hero.  I was assigned to Betty Gales...I have had only one call, yes, one initial call so far and WOW, the difference I see already in myself.   I stopped drinking soda!  I have never been able to achieve more than 3 days without soda, its been over a week due to our conversations about looking yourself in the mirror etc.  She made me feel that not only was she trying to get to know me, but she made me feel she needed to understand my current situation.  She requested information from me that honestly took me back a little that she was asking for such items, she asked for a very detailed and honest breakdown of business and personal monthly debts. She needed to understand my history and my current situation in order to put a plan of action together for my future.  "I think she was seeing how honest I would be and to see if she had someone willing to put myself out there which would show her that I am ready for her to rock my business and my future.  She made me feel that she is willing to start at the core of "my life" in order to understand how to achieve the goals that I have placed in myself.  She is hard yet soft...she reminds me of someone that will be nice to me unless I let us both down then she will come out like a boxer...AND THIS IS AFTER ONLY ONE CALL.
Tom Ferry, I cant imagine you lucky you must feel to have someone like Betty on your team!
One last thing I would like to add about my initial experience of coaching is the life by design video series and workbook assignments, I have had several Oprah "aha" moments. at my 6 months mark, I will do another review.

Review of Shift! Event:
Great insights in an intimate setting!  Terrific venue for learning new material.
It should be billed as a follow on to Blueprint...
1. Thoughtful insights into laying groundwork for core values and growing a company not just a “practice”.
2. Great training about keeping new agents on track with insightful coaching.
3. Marketing truisms from Jay Abraham were informative and terrific.
4. Breakthrough formula on hiring and tested on-boarding practices from Mark Roberge was very informative and he backed up everything he said with examples.
5. Treasure Davis IS a treasure! Her heart shows through in everything she has built. Loved her work and attitude! She was fabulous and even made it through glitches on a power point with flying colors. Can’t say enough good things about her talk but more importantly her warmth and care for others.  So many insights and tips!
6. Mathew Ferrara was warm, funny, genuine and a bit quirky. Loved him! He got across the idea of “story brand”... his stories explained why we needed to do the core values exercise and define leadership to us too.</Review>

Tom Ferry, his company, and our personal coach, David Parker, all kick major ass!!!

Tom Ferry
If Tom is one word, it’s innovative. Being an agent in my 30s I wanted innovation in technology, marketing and client communication… but not in arbitrary ways. I wanted this innovation to improve my productivity and allow me to better serve my real estate clients. Tom provides this. Not just sometimes, not just at some events, but ALL THE DAMN TIME! He and his creative team are constantly enhancing our business coaching experience through providing incredible content at in-person training events, launching systems and strategies that increase agent productivity and effectiveness of marketing, or being ten steps ahead of trends in the market.

Company
What a team Tom has supporting him! From his incredible coaches, to his powerful speakers, to his customer service, to his creative development team… All of them are operating at a high level. Our personal customer service representative, Douglas May, is awesome. He’s always available, enthusiastic, and encouraging.

Our Coach, David
I absolutely love working with David Parker. Not only is he massively accomplished in his family life, business life and personal life, but he’s incredibly humble about it all. From furthering his university education to achieving second degree blackbelt status to conscientiously ensuring he spends time with his family, this guy is a true well rounded individual and inspiration. Many business coaching companies or training programs focus on working an agent to death and encourage solely focusing on the money making aspect of real estate. Instead, David, and the Tom Ferry organization, are holistic in their approach to client development. They believe that health and vitality are key foundations and from that anything can be constructed with the right plan and mindset!

While I’ve only worked with David and the Tom Ferry organization for a hand full of months, I am excited to see what the future holds with this incredibly innovative company, Tom Ferry’s awesome in-person events and our inspirational, personal business coach.

Living at Level 10!</Review>

<review>Tom Ferry is definitely not worth the money! Once you sign a contract say goodbye to $6,000. You are better off using this money to market yourself. They promised me that I would make X amount of dollars and if I didn't then they would give me my money back- but of course they do not give you full disclosure. They told me I missed a coaching call (which my coach also missed calls when I called in) and I didn't attend a seminar in Las Vegas (which cost even more $) and so I do not qualify to get any money back. As a new agent I got sucked into this and thought I need to spend money on my education and etc.. I would not do this again if I had a choice and know what I know now. Watch the free videos online, read books, attend seminars, classes (even Sales Edge) you can learn the same information for much less. If you need an accountability partner find one in your office. Overall- not worth the money!</review>< pics>

<text>Prior to joining Tom Ferry Coaching, I was pondering and pretty much procrastinating about the whole idea. Something we're all guilty of and do everyday right? So I just figured a simple conversation and my questions answered wont hurt...let me try my free 1 hour session and see how I feel about it all. Maybe this isn't for me. Cheryl Ingraham a coaching consultant called me and took me to a place and asked me questions no one ever has before. One light bulb after the other was going off. This was beyond me being aware of what I wanted in life, it was about who I am now, who I was, where am I going vs where I want to go. A total self discovery happened that I had no idea existed. She wasn't just listening, she understood. She helped me discover my "WHY". After I hung up with her, I took about a good week thinking in extreme deep thought about our conversation. Nothing was on my mind other than Cheryl and our conversation. She followed up with me, ask how I was doing. Genuinely wanted to know how I was doing as a human being. And she simply left it at that. I took another week, I picked up the phone and asked to speak with her, she made herself available to take the call. We chatted again, she said a few words of complete and utter encouragement. But it didn't stop there. She helped me discover that I can believe in myself. She taught me self patience. It was that boost that you get from your big sister to climb over the wall. That was all I needed. I knew that if I didn't join a network of like minded people with like minded goals I was going to feel the same burdens with the same thoughts and most likely be in the same position. Since I took the leap of faith and signed up in November of 2017, I started to read the books and listen to the audios she recommended. I started to love myself a little more and think more positively. I slowly started to eat right, and do little changes. Cheryl let me be raw and honest about how things really were vs where in my heart I wanted to be. I was stressed, I didn't know what was going to happen, I felt I was drowning. Jan of 2018 I had surgery that took me back 6 weeks in bed. Cheryl said to read, listen to audio and to start to put my systems in place, whatever I could do from bed. She still believed in me. Im thinking she's completely nuts!!! I'm spending the first half of Q1 in bed?? How in the heck am I supposed to catch up??? Cheryl kept in touch, she asked how I was doing, she kept recommending videos to watch and stayed on me about letting go and positive thinking. Low and behold, one day a sale literally fell on my lap. It was the purchase of my very first home. Jan 25 2018. I don't know what happened but I had the opportunity to not only have a sale but my own home???? This is crazy!!!! no way!! My landlord comes to me and simply says, "Sell my home" WHAT???? ok that was easy... AND I BOUGHT IT!! How did this happen? That was the just the beginning. My escrow went so smooth, I still can't even tell you how this happened. I told Cheryl. She said keep reading and keep thinking positive. She shared more insight. Low and behold, a buyer. "I want that house!" he says, smooth escrow. Now I have a few dollars in my pocket. My life is starting to lighten up. I am homeowner for the first time, and leads are coming in like crazy! Breakthrough by design gave me step by step instructions on how to handle all of this. I'm thinking Tom Ferry is a genius, why didn't I do this long time ago???? It's true what they say : The pain of discipline or the pain of regret. I feel both today. If it wasn't for Cheryl Ingraham, and my faith in God, I don't see how my life would have changed for the better. A new home, 2 closed sales, 1 currently in escrow, a new car and my boyfriend proposes to me all in a matter 9 weeks!!! WTH??!!! Yes my friends all is possible. If you feel doubt, call Cheryl over at Tom Ferry Origination and have faith of just a mustard seed. I'm living proof!! <Text>Although I have never met Tom personally I understand his mindset. I joined his organization for me, not because his hype lured me in. < Text>
I received a call three years ago that changed my life. Another sales rep working for a coaching company that promised me the world. This rep was Cale Hogue. Someone now that I consider a friend (I owe him everything). I started coaching with 6 sales under my belt and a few months of real estate experience. I was off to a great start. I looked around my office and most of the agents were doing 10-20 deals a year and were completely satisfied with that amount. I knew there had to be other agents out there that wanted more. So... I took to Google. After endless free 1/2 day conferences, I discovered a program by Tom Ferry called Breakthrough By Design. Best $300 I ever invested.

After I enrolled in Breakthrough By Design, Cale gave me a call to discuss Tom Ferry and their coaching programs. At first I was hesitant and didn't sign up. How do you know something will work if you've never experienced it before and when you are a brand new realtor, opportunities for sales gimmicks are thrown at you left and right. Needless to say, I signed up after the second time Cale called me and I joined Core. At $600 a month I was nervous and excited. After a few months I wasn't noticing a difference and I wanted to quit. I called Cale and complained about my situation. He said that I just need to trust him and it will work.  After one year in Core coaching I was taught a huge lesson... There is no magic formula. Theres hard work and theres determination. When you allow yourself to become part of the ecosystem and open up to others within coaching, thats when the magic happens. Through Core Coaching, I was able to close 24 deals my first full year in the business and become top 1% of realtors in San Diego County.

I decided that I was seeing results from my coaching that I wanted to increase my number of calls so I upgraded to Elite+. With a call every week, my coach and I were able to get to know each other and develop the plan to start my very own real estate team. My coach Alyssia Essig had me on a strict plan to improve my sphere of influence and really get the systems in place. I hired my first assistant and buyers agent with the help of my coach. She guided me through who to hire and what to look for. She kept me on track and guided me through a lot of fear.

Last year at the Elite+ Retreat in Palm Desert, I joined Team+. My Elite+ coach Alyssia Essig forced me to up my accountability and jump into team coaching head first. Another huge step and I didn't think I was ready for it. I was about to enter the level of coaching that all the people I looked up to were a part of.

I was assigned Mike Schumm as my Team+ coach. I was scared of this man and I knew it was the perfect coach for me. Mike is over qualified to be spending his time with me. He runs two successful teams in the NE and has been in the business for years. Mike doesn't do coaching for the money. He can make much more selling real estate. He does this because he wants to give back. Thats what I love about Tom Ferry. The coaches he obtains are always top notch and are doing this because they care.

Tom Ferry coaching is more than just your one on one calls with your coach. It's the mastermind groups you form that you are able to share with, its the facebook groups that provide endless value, and its the friendships that make it so special.  You begin to make life long friends with your coach and your peers. There are always going to be someone that says Tom Ferry coaching or even coaching doesn't work. This isn't 6 minute abs. Coaching works! And Tom Ferry Coaching is the best. This review is corny and its because Tom Ferry Coaching changed my life. This year I will net just over $1 million. Talk about life changing.<//Text>
